  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need e-Residency to get the Digital Nomad Visa?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No. e-Residency and the DN visa are completely separate programs. e-Residency is for running a digital business in the EU; the DN visa is for physical residence. You can have one, both, or neither.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I pay Estonian taxes?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          If you stay 183+ days and become a tax resident, you may have Estonian tax obligations. However, as a DN visa holder working for foreign employers, your situation is complex—consult an Estonian tax advisor.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I travel in the Schengen Area?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. Estonia is a Schengen member. Your DN visa allows travel throughout the 27-country Schengen zone, making Europe very accessible.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How's the internet in Estonia?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Excellent. Estonia pioneered digital government and has some of the best internet infrastructure in Europe. Free WiFi is widely available, and fiber connections are common in apartments.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is English widely spoken?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, especially in Tallinn and among younger Estonians. English proficiency is very high. You can navigate daily life entirely in English, though learning Estonian phrases is appreciated.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I extend the DN visa beyond 1 year?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          The DN visa is valid for up to 1 year. After that, you'd need to apply for a different residence permit or leave and potentially reapply. It's not automatically renewable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

